# Let's categorize the Age_groups for better understanding of visualization later on
# Based on research
# I can specify that: child(<13), teen(>=13), early_adulthood(20-29), adulthood(30-39), middle_age(40-59), early_elder(60-69), elders(>=70)

'''65 + == early elders and elderly
60 - 64 == early elders
50 - 54 == middle aged
40 - 44 == middle aged
55 - 59 == middle aged
45 - 49 == middle aged
18 - 24 == teen and early adulthood
25 - 34 == early adulthood and adulthood
'''

# Hence i will map all the specified age categories to the column

df['Age_groups'] = df['Age_groups'].map({'18 - 24': 'teen and early adulthood', 
                                         '25 - 34': 'early adulthood and adulthood',
                                         '40 - 44':'middle aged',
                                         '45 - 49':'middle aged',
                                         '50 - 54':'middle aged',
                                         '55 - 59':'middle aged',
                                         '60 - 64':'early elders',
                                         '65 +':'early elders and elderly',
                                         })

# A wordcloud for the most common words
stopwords = set(STOPWORDS)
def wordcloud(data, title = None):
    wordcloud = WordCloud(
        background_color='white',
        stopwords=stopwords,
        max_words=250,
        max_font_size=30,
        scale=2,
        random_state=5 #chosen a andom by flipping a coin; it was heads
).generate(str(data))

    fig = plt.figure(1, figsize=(15, 15))
    plt.axis('off')
    if title: 
        fig.suptitle(title, fontsize=20)
        fig.subplots_adjust(top=2.3)
    plt.imshow(wordcloud)
    plt.show()

OBSERVATIONS¶

  • Single people are in need of loans more that others
  • Lagos has the highest number of borrowers, this can be a factor to get more borrowers i.e the more we patronise people from this location the higher our chances of increasing cutomers.
  • Early elders and elderly do not borrow as frequently as the rest age groups
  • Many prefeer the disbursement of loans through the mobile app
  • Males take loans more than females do
  • Those with higher incomes take more loans
  • The word cloud shows that customers are more likely to refer a Lender if they provide faster services and service charges
  • The word cloud shows that customers are more likely to drop their work information and bank statement to get a loan
  • Those with average income take more loans than others
  • The heatmap shows that there is almost a strong positive correlation between number of dependants and Taking a loan
  • The heatmap shows that there is almost a strong positive correlation between number of dependants and monthly income

LIMITATIONS¶

  • The actual income of lenders would have aided the investigation more as to who would get more loans
  • More numerical values would prove to be helpful with prediction and correlation
  • More data is to be added to this dataset to improve model prediction and correlation
  • Invallid responses made by borrowers
